SoD Check
Flags potential access risks
The SoD check enables users to determine potential risks associated with their planned business roles.
The access analysis service has a predefined set of parameters for SoD (segregation of duties) risks and critical access risks, which is delivered with SAP S/4 HANA Cloud by default.
It analyzes all access associated with the business roles against parameters such as risk, risk type, and risk level, and flags any potential risk or violations.
For example:
Systems Security and Configurations access would be flagged as a potential critical access risk.
You would then decide whether it is still appropriate to assign this access to the role.
A role with access for Vendor Maintenance and Posting Invoices would be flagged as having a SoD risk, as you would not want a person with the ability to both approve and pay vendors.
The information from the access analysis helps prevent potential access risks from entering your system, and by identifying the risks it enables you to make informed decisions on the access to include in your business roles.
For more information, search for Product Overview:
Access Analysis Service and Integration Scenario:
SAP S/4 HANA Cloud in your version of Access Analysis Service on SAP Help Portal.
