Deferrals and Installment Plans
You can ether defer the payment or arrange an installment plan in the case of business partners that cannot not comply with their payment obligations.
You can calculate interest for installment plans.
If a deferral has been agreed, a deferral date is noted in the open item in addition to the due date.
The deferral date has the effect that the system neither duns nor collects payments provided that the agreed deferral period is valid.
Once the deferral date has passed without payment being made, the open item is dunned and bank collection is executed again.
If payment by installments has been agreed, you create an installment plan for the amount of the original receivable.
The individual installments and their due dates are specified in the installment plan.
You can levy charges for the facility of offering an installment plan.
To avoid having due dates fall at the weekend or on public holidays, you can refer to the factory calendar when determining these dates.
The dunning run and the payment run take into account the individual installments in the installment plan instead of the original receivable.
You can delete installments that have not yet been paid, and change the amount of an installment (repayment and interest) or the due date.
You can add installments to an active installment plan.
The sum of the installments in an installment plan must always be correspond to the sum of the original receivables entered in the installment plan.
Provided the installment plan is active, in the account balance display and the installment plan, you can call up the receivables in an installment.
The document number of the installment plan is recorded in the original receivables.
This enables the link between the original receivables and the installment plan to be guaranteed.
When an installment is paid, the payment is automatically distributed among the source receivables.
When the final installment of an installment plan is paid, both the installment plan and the original receivable are cleared by means of the payment run when the incoming payment is posted.
Installments can be partially paid.
If the agreement for payment in installments is canceled, you can deactivate the installment plan manually.
This means that the original receivable becomes active again.
The system removes the link between the original receivable and the installment plan.
A deactivated installment plan cannot be reactivated and you can also no longer assign payments to the installment plan.
With appropriate Customizing settings for the installment plan categories, you can update the creditworthiness of the business partner concerned when you create an installment plan.
By means of the appropriate configuration of the deactivation reasons, you can reverse the creditworthiness entries again.
