No Processing Required
Moves items that do not need processing from Moved Out to Process History.
Items that were Moved Out can be either corrected and resent or reversed.
For documents that cannot be corrected and resent, a reversal document must be submitted to the partner system.
In this case, both documents appear under Moved Out.
For example, you submitted item 001, but the tax amount was incorrect.
As a result, you had to submit item 002 to your partner system to reverse item 001.
Both of these items are listed under Moved Out.
Moved Out is a temporary holding place for items that you need to edit and resend.
However, you cannot edit and resend reversal documents.
If no further processing is required, as is the case with reversal documents, you can select No Processing Required.
Once you confirm that you want to mark the item in question as Reverted, it is moved out from Moved Out and into Process History.
That way, you know that you don't need to maintain that item and can instead focus on other items in Moved Out that can be edited and resent.
Please note that this status is set only once an item has been checked and determined that it cannot be edited and resubmitted.
